<node><name>Introduce Activity</name>
<id>3</id>
<lefticon>undefined</lefticon>
<righticon>orchestration</righticon>
<column>ICI</column>
<textHTML>&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Review the the principle of superposition, describing standing waves on a string and in a pipe. Highlight that the 2 waves interfering are confined in space (i.e. on the string and in a pipe)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Initiate Class Discussion&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;</textHTML>
<linkedwf>undefined</linkedwf>
<textheight>132</textheight>
<isdropped>true</isdropped>
</node>
<node><name>Discuss Applications of the Principle</name>
<id>5</id>
<lefticon>class</lefticon>
<righticon>discuss</righticon>
<column>ICS</column>
<textHTML>&lt;p&gt;Discuss prompts given by the instructor:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Imagine: Two identical waves coming from two sources. At any location where the two waves meet, they will interfere. Consider specific conditions that lead to Constructive Interference and Destructive Interference using math&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Answer: What should be expected if this idea is mimicked right now? What would be heard? Would what they hear vary depending on where they are?&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;</textHTML>
<linkedwf>undefined</linkedwf>
<textheight>202</textheight>
<isdropped>true</isdropped>
</node>
<node><name>Demonstrate Interference</name>
<id>6</id>
<lefticon>undefined</lefticon>
<righticon>orchestration</righticon>
<column>ICI</column>
<textHTML>&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Set up 1 signal generator with a sinusoidal signal feeding the 2 speakers (e.g. use 240 Hz)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Direct students to walk around the room experiencing the interference creating the variation in volume throughout the room&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;Note: If time permits, students can also try to find the wavelength using a meter stick, and then estimate the speed of sound.&lt;/p&gt;</textHTML>
<linkedwf>undefined</linkedwf>
<textheight>174</textheight>
<isdropped>true</isdropped>
</node>
<node><name>Estimate Locations of Interference</name>
<id>8</id>
<lefticon>class</lefticon>
<righticon>problem</righticon>
<column>ICS</column>
<textHTML>&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Try to estimate locations of CON and DES&amp;nbsp;interference&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Calculate the wave length using the speed of sound and the frequency used&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;</textHTML>
<linkedwf>undefined</linkedwf>
<textheight>104</textheight>
<isdropped>true</isdropped>
</node>
<node><name>Set up New Conditions for Interference</name>
<id>9</id>
<lefticon>undefined</lefticon>
<righticon>orchestration</righticon>
<column>ICI</column>
<textHTML>&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Direct students to step outside of the room&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Explain the parallel to what will be covered in a few weeks (i.e. Diffraction)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Return to the room to modify the frequency &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Direct students to return to the room to make predictions about the interference&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;Note: May change the frequency a third time and repeat the process.&lt;/p&gt;</textHTML>
<linkedwf>undefined</linkedwf>
<textheight>188</textheight>
<isdropped>true</isdropped>
